ckish bill with a pale lower mandible and pale brownish legs. Voice The territorial call is a rarely heard harsh and rapid chattering. It trills constantly when foraging. It joins the morning chorus with a dull monotonous and rhythmic \"whup-whup-whup\" sand from a perch before and at the start of the breeding season. Distribution Western Africa from extreme southern Mauritania and Senegal to north western Cameroon, south-western Chad and far north-western Central African Republic. Habits and habitat The Senegal eremomela occurs in small parties which actively forage in wooded savanna, cultivated areas and orchards. It is arboreal and insectivorous feeding on ants, beetles, caterpillars and other larvae, as well as some fruit. It breeds in the first half of the year in the west, although egg laying has been recorded as late as October in the Ivory Coast. References Birds of The Gambia by Barlow, Wacher and Disley, ISBN 1-873403-32-1 External links Recordings of the Senegal Eremomela at Xeno-Canto", "shortSummary": "The Senegal eremomela (Eremomela pusilla) is a member of the African warbler family, the Cisticolidae. It occurs in the savannas of western…", "locations": ["撒哈拉以南非洲", "科特迪瓦"], "habitats": ["稀树草原"], "lat": 8.0, "lng": -5.0, "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/56/Senegal_Erememola_-_Gambia_%2832496575342%29.jpg/960px-Senegal_Erememola_-_Gambia_%2832496575342%29.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-eremomela", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-eremomela-pusilla", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-eremomela", "species": "taxonomy-species-eremomela-pusilla"}, "expandable": true, "x": 994.69, "y": -253.2, "z": 694.86}], "links": [{"key": "bird-senegal-eremomela-30020db1__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species